kpi_info.title: period_duration
kpi_info.use: Duration of the measurement period in minutes.

kpi_info.title: utran_not_able_exec_ishho_rt
kpi_info.use: Number of inter-system handover failures for RT due to UTRAN. --- The failure can occur, for example, due to the following reasons: relocation preparation procedure failure in the CN, or relocation resource allocation procedure failure in the target BSC.

kpi_info.title: ue_not_able_exec_ishho_rt
kpi_info.use: "Number of times when during inter-system handover for RT the source RNC has ordered the UE to use a configuration which the UE does not support. --- If the source RNC instructs the UE to use a configuration that it does not support, the UE will send a failure message to the source RNC. The handover procedure ends and the UE resumes normal operation as if no handover attempt had occurred."

kpi_info.title: is_com_mod_sta_not_pos_rt
kpi_info.use: "The number of times when it is not possible to start inter-system (inter-RAT) compressed mode measurement due to radio resource congestion, BTS, or UE related reasons."

kpi_info.title: is_hho_w_cmod_ul_dch_q_rt
kpi_info.use: The number of inter-system HHO decisions after measuring with compressed mode due to uplink DCH quality - by UEs with RT connection. HC triggers the start of inter-system measurements for a UE due to the fact that a quality deterioration report from outer loop power control is obtained. The measurement is enabled by the parameter GSMcauseUplinkQuality.

kpi_info.title: unsucc_is_hho_ul_dch_q_rt
kpi_info.use: "The number of unsuccessful inter-system handovers caused by uplink DCH quality for RT. --- If the UE fails to establish the physical channel(s) indicated in the handover command, the UE will revert to the configuration prior to the reception of the handover command (old configuration) and transmit a failure message to the source RNC. UPDATED: When the radio connection is lost during inter system handover procedure and the radio links are deleted.

kpi_info.title: SUCC_IS_HHO_DR_AMR_RT
kpi_info.use: The number of successful inter-system handovers caused by Directed Retry for AMR calls. UPDATED: When the RNC receives an RANAP: IU RELEASE COMMAND message with a normal release cause from the CN - when inter-system handover procedure is ongoing. This counter is updated only when the trigger reason is Directed Retry for AMR call.

kpi_info.title: UNSUCC_IS_HHO_DR_AMR_RT
kpi_info.use: The number of unsuccessful inter-system handovers caused by Directed Retry for AMR calls. If the UE fails to establish the physical channel(s) indicated in the handover command, the UE will revert to the configuration prior to the reception of the handover command (old configuration) and transmit a failure message to the source RNC. From end user point of view a failure in Directed Retry triggered ISHO means a failed CS Voice call attempt. UPDATED: When the RNC receives an RRC: HANDOVER FROM UTRAN FAILURE message from the UE, and the failure cause is not "configuration unacceptable". This counter is updated only when the trigger reason is Directed Retry for AMR call.

UPDATED: When the radio connection is lost during inter system handover procedure and the radio links are deleted.
